### Describe the bug

I want to create a minimal API returning `IAsyncEnumerable<T>` to be used as a source of server-side events. If I do this via controller, this works fine:
```
public class JobsController() : ControllerBase
{

    [HttpGet("api/v1/jobs/{jobId}/status/stream")]
    [ProducesResponseType(typeof(JobStatus), (int)HttpStatusCode.OK, "text/event-stream")]
    public async IAsyncEnumerable<JobStatus> GetStatusStream(Guid jobId, [EnumeratorCancellation] CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        Response.Headers.ContentType = "text/event-stream";

        for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++)
        {
            await Task.Delay(500, cancellationToken);
            yield return new JobStatus(10, i + 1);
        }
    }

}

public record JobStatus(int TotalTasksCount, int CompletedTasksCount);
```
The response type is correcly set to `text/event-stream`.

With the minimal API (see Reposroduction steps section), however, this does not work as intended. After the content-type header is set within the method, it gets overwritten in `HttpResponseJsonExtensions`
(https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/blob/825daf664804598df9942499970bee5e0f2432d5/src/Http/Http.Extensions/src/HttpResponseJsonExtensions.cs#L91) which is called with `contentType = null` from `ExecuteHandlerHelper`(https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/blob/825daf664804598df9942499970bee5e0f2432d5/src/Shared/RouteHandlers/ExecuteHandlerHelper.cs#L56).
So the actual `Content-type` of the response becomes `application/json; utf-8`, and SSE simply does not work.

Is there any way to return `IAsyncEnumerable<T>` from a minimal API endpoint with content-type `text/event-stream`?

### Expected Behavior

To not override Content-type of the reponse if it is set in the user code.

### Steps To Reproduce

```
        endpointRouteBuilder.MapGet("api/v1/jobs/{jobId}/status/stream2", (
            Guid jobId,
            HttpContext httpContext,
            CancellationToken cancellationToken) =>
        {
            httpContext.Response.Headers.ContentType = "text/event-stream";
            return GetStatusStream(cancellationToken);
        });

        private async IAsyncEnumerable<JobStatus> GetStatusStream([EnumeratorCancellation] CancellationToken cancellationToken)
        {
            for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++)
            {
                await Task.Delay(500, cancellationToken);
                yield return new JobStatus(10, i + 1);
            }
        }
```

### Exceptions (if any)

No.

### .NET Version

net 8.0

